description: For sale: $105,000. Alpine Elite condo is the largest of all the condos and just short of being called a townhome with the amount of space it offers, you could live here! Caribou Highlands Resort sits within the Lutsen Mtns Ski Area where one can ski in - ski out returning back for lunch in the comfort of your condo or at the on-site restaurant. Stay and play in this one bedroom unit with an open sleeping loft, unit sleeps six. Relax while enjoying your favorite beverage in front of the fireplace or on the deck while taking in the stunning view of Moose Mtn. This four season resort will care for many of the details leaving you to enjoy the on-site amenities including swimming pool, hot tub, exercise facility and/or as a jump off to visit your nearby favorite hangouts. Furnishings are included! Come see this Alpine Elite condo with its GREAT views of Lutsen Mountains. Invest in Minnesota's North Shore, a favorite Minnesota destination for skiing, hiking and just hanging out! Call now for a showing!

description: For sale: $549,000. Meander down the Cascade Beach Road in Lutsen to this lovely Lake Superior cottage, where you will forget all about your worries! Sweet and simple design, with charm dating back to the late 60's, but nicely updated with newer windows, deck and updated interior living spaces. The main level has 3 bedrooms, and a very nice bathroom. The kitchen is cute as can be, with nice views of Lake Superior from the kitchen sink. The living room is cozy with a ton of windows, a wood burning fireplace and walk out slider to a fantastic deck.  We are betting you will spend most of your summer days on the deck, it's really something to experience. Lofted above the lake, the views are astounding. And what a sense of seclusion you feel! No other homes in sight, only the wilderness and the Big Lake! Wander down the path to the lower level walk out, which serves as Rec space for your guests to enjoy with a second bathroom and laundry.  Odds are you'll skip the visit to the lower level and head right to the incredible ledge rock shoreline, made for meandering and climbing around on the really nice ledge that gently stretches in to Lake Superior.  Launch your kayaks on a calm day, dip your toes in the water, or enjoy a campfire down at the lake and create your own memories along Lutsen's Lake Superior shoreline. A Must See home.

description: For sale: $489,900. *Showing requests are generally not being approved at this time; Buyer's agents may contact listing agent directly to discuss requests and alternate options.*    Make it a point to see this gorgeous milled log home with prow, tucked into a perfect setting within the Superior National at Lutsen golf community. Open concept great room with cobblestone fireplace, plus a four-season porch all in a woodsy setting. Perfect layout for entertaining and cooking, with peninsula bar and newer stainless appliances. Main floor owner's suite with separate tub and shower. Main floor laundry for convenience. Two bedrooms are on the upper level, with shared full bath, and a casual loft area for plenty of room to spread out with family & friends. In-floor heat with electric boiler, plus a propane-fueled FP offering dual fuel savings. Large wraparound deck facing Lake Superior, complete with a neat outdoor gear closet.  Oversized, detached double garage, and a cool firepit. This is a well-maintained home with great curb appeal, located on the 5th fairway of the River 9 course. Well-managed HOA with shared state-certified water and waste systems. This is a perfect location to enjoy all of the activities the North Shore has to offer. Golf at Superior National, ski at Lutsen Mtns, bike the Gitche Gumee trail, numerous trails for hiking or snowshoeing, and the magnificent Lake Superior nearby. Close to restaurants, shops and within walking distance of North Shore Winery!  Call today for your private showing.

description: For sale: $319,000. This Poplar Ridge Home at Caribou Highlands is a Must see! Super desirable location for winter and summer activities. The ski trails are right out the front door, and snowmobiling and hiking is nearby. This is unique townhome, because it offers 5th bedroom and sauna in the lower level, along with kitchenette. Another bedroom for sleeping extra guests which means in total you can sleep 14 people! Great space for relaxation and games or just relaxing after a day full of activities. Check out the walk-out Patio and built in swing! The main level is the ultimate hang out spot. There is Private Master Suite with separate shower and Jacuzzi, private deck and gas fireplace! The family room offers gas fireplace (super-efficient), updated kitchen opened floor plan, dining area and large deck with outdoor grill and sitting area! The upper level is all about sleeping with a large bedroom to sleep the kids with access to a full bathroom. There is also another Master bedroom with its own private ¾ of a bathroom -Offering amazing mountain views. Custom furnishings - wood work stands out, sound proof shared wall with another unit. The resort offers many amenities - 2 swimming pools - indoor and outdoor swimming fun! There is hot tub in the indoor swimming pool area, game area and kid's room for scheduled activities! There is exercise room if you still have energy after full day of hiking, skiing, snowmobiling or visiting the State parks and falls in the area. Check out the view of Moose Mountain from the private deck! The Association has solid long term Maintenance Reserve Plan and Capital Improvement reserves.

description: For sale: $105,000. Alpine Elite condo is the largest of all the condos and just short of being called a town home with the amount of space it offers, you could live here!  Caribou Highlands Resort sits within the Lutsen Mtns Ski Area where one can ski in - ski out returning back for lunch in the comfort of your condo or at the on-site restaurant.  Stay and play in this one bedroom unit with an open sleeping loft, unit sleeps six.  Relax while enjoying your favorite beverage in front of the fireplace or on the deck while taking in the stunning view of Moose Mtn.  This four season resort will care for many of the details leaving you to enjoy the on-site amenities including swimming pool, hot tub, exercise facility and/or as a jump off to visit your nearby favorite hangouts.  Furnishings are included! Come see this Alpine Elite condo with its GREAT views of Lutsen Mountains.  Invest in Minnesota's North Shore, a favorite Minnesota destination for skiing, hiking and just hanging out!

description: For sale: $698,500. Cascade Beach! Secluded Lake Superior Year Round Retreat At Waters Edge W/309 Ft Dramatic Ledgerock Beach & Incredible Water Views! Set back off paved Scenic 61 on 5 acres--deep lot w/no road noise just bird calls & waves crashing on the shore. Ideal location only 10 mi S to ski & golf at Lutsen & 10 mi N to Grand Marais & the BWCAW. 1903 SF, 2+BR/1BTH knotty pine home w/2 stall garage. Vaulted great room w/pegged oak floor, massive cobblestone fireplace & floor-ceiling glass lakeside open to wrap around deck. Kitchen open to great rm & water view. 2 main flr BRs. Main flr BTH. Main flr laundry. Spacious loft w/room for at least 2 beds. Basement for utilities & storage. Economical propane forced air furnace. Skip rocks, hunt driftwood, take a peaceful walk or bike ride, relax in front of the fireplace & enjoy the magnificent play of light and shadows across the water from your wonderful relaxing nest! Click on link to view 3D Tour!

description: For sale: $349,900. Charming cabin on Caribou Lake with almost 200 ft of shoreline! Great Peninsula Point location! Current owner purchased the land in 1936 and built the cabin in 1980 and garage in 1989! Fabulous Lake views from cozy living room with massive brick wood burning fire place! Wrap around deck for outdoor living in the summer and fall! The main floor features two bedrooms and full bathroom -very functional. New owner can put their own vision and touches and make the space their own. Home has great bones, and very nice cedar siding. The lower level has tucked under small garage space for parking snowmobiles, 4 wheelers or boats. Great size Loft with completely enclosed Master Suite with half a bathroom. The detached garage has a great slab and is insulated with large bunkroom upstairs, accessed by interior staircase!

description: For sale: $489,900. This 4 bedroom, 4 bath home sits on over 6 acres of cedar, birch, and pine with amazing Lake Superior views. Enter a huge foyer with india slate tiled floors leading to the true definition of an open floor plan. The expansive dining room and living room are flooded with natural light from the floor to ceiling (2-stories) windows. Hickory floors flow from there into the enormous kitchen area.  Custom hickory cabinets, stainless steel appliances, and yards of jurassic black granite counters make this kitchen a pleasant place to cook. Adjoining the kitchen is an inviting office space. A main floor media room with a full wall of built-in shelves is space to hang out. There is a main floor laundry with plenty of storage and a unigue half bath right off the foyer.  The spacious main floor master bedroom has large windows, walk-in closet and private bathroom with tub and separate shower accented by tiling that is a work of art. Up stairs there are two generously sized bedrooms with large windows and nice closets.  The second floor full bathroom has a tiled floor, modern vessel sink and large storage area. The loft lounge area, with its juliet balcony, is a perfect location to just soak in the beauty of Lake Superior. There is  an additional living space on the basement level that includes a bedroom, living room, kitchen, 3/4 bath and its own laundry. With its private entry and lots of southern windows this space can be an income space or a great guest apartment. The attached garage has overhead storage. This exceptional property was designed for retirement with privacy and everything you need on one level. The abundant windows light every room and give you continued opportunity to enjoy the incredible Lake Superior view.  All your favorite outdoor activities are close by.  Its just waiting for you to make it your own!

description: For sale: $79,900. Make this Sweet One bedroom Condo your basecamp to all that Lutsen offers! Spend your summer hiking the mountains, enjoying the Alpine Slide at Lutsen Mountains Resort and then Ski your Winters Away at this Ski In Ski Out Condo! Enjoy a cup of coffee or a book on the brand new private deck, overlooking Lake Superior and Moose Mountain! Rental management program is in place if you are looking to offset some of the expenses, or you can keep for your own year round Enjoyment! The exterior of the building and decks were completely redone! The building has a new roof. The amenities include indoor and outdoor swimming pool, restaurant on site with wide selection of locally crafted beer, front desk, gift shop, SPA.

description: For sale: $315,000. Lutsen Living at it's Best! Look to the West at the backside of Ulr Mountain at Lutsen Mountains Ski & Summer Resort! This lodge style home is in an easily accessible location while feeling very serene and peaceful. 5 acres of wilderness bordering Superior National Forest land, a ravine with small creek flows nearby the  home. Fantastic Sauna just off the deck completes the Northwoods package. For the Outdoor Enthusiast, enjoy easy access via a private drive to the Local Groomed Cross Country Ski Trails, local Snowmobile Trails, and tons of lakes within minutes. The interior of the cabin is stylish and comfortable. Kitchen is large enough to accommodate family gatherings, with granite counters and built in breakfast bar. Be sure to check out the pantry! Dining area open to family room and kitchen, a nice space for entertaining friends.  Main level guest bedroom, with adjoining den with wood burning fireplace. You will love to cozy up to the fireplace in the winter and enjoy a good book! Master bedroom suite has distant Lake Superior views with Super master bath! Two additional bedrooms with bath complete the home. Two car attached heated garage, plus a detached garage with side covered boat storage. This is a wonderful Lutsen Wilderness home in a fabulous location!

description: For sale: $535,000. Dip down from Highway 61 to this peaceful Lutsen Lakeside Oasis! Built before the days of lakeshore setbacks, this home is perched just at the edge of the ledgerock leading to Lake Superior. Well designed home allows the Big Lake to be the Big Focus! Kitchen, Dining, Great room and two of the three bedrooms all have excellent views of Lake Superior. Vaulted open ceilings welcome you in to the home. The galley style kitchen has plenty of space for family gatherings, opening in to the dining area. Sunken Great room features a rare basalt stone fireplace in the center of the room. Large windows run the length of the home allowing for many hours of Lake Superior viewing from different vantage points. The lakeside deck allows you to feel like you're on a ship floating across the big lake.  Inside, the spaces are comfortable and modern feeling. Functional in design, the hallway leads to two guest bedrooms and full bath, and to the master bedroom with en suite 3/4 bath. Enjoy morning sunrises from your bed! Just a wonderful home in Lutsen on Lake Superior, move in ready for your enjoyment! One plus car attached garage, lovely surroundings with a good sense of seclusion. Just two driveways away from the west end of the Cascade Beach Rd, perfect Lutsen location!

streetAddress: 515 Poplar River Road Lutsen Resort Lake Superior
description: For sale: $399,000. Poplar River 515 is a 3BR, 3BA luxury condominium on Lake Superior. This Poplar River unit is part of the Lutsen Resort vacation rental program that offers a unique opportunity for multiple rental options with 3 lock out units. Outstanding views of Lake Superior from every room of this 1800 sf condo that sits on the hillside adjacent to the Poplar River with its rapids and waterfalls. Living Room, full Kitchen and Dining Room have an open concept floor plan that includes a deck for grilling and/or enjoying a favorite beverage. Each bedroom unit has a master bath, a king or two queen beds, and fireplace. Wet bars are also included in the two end units. Walking distance away is the historic main lodge with its two restaurants, indoor pool, sauna, hot tub, and an endless list of recreation opportunities available on the 600' of shared Lake Superior shoreline.

description: For sale: $374,900. Winter lovers here is your Lutsen Home! Located just 13 miles up the Caribou Trail in Lutsen, (less than 20 miles from Lutsen Mountains Ski and Summer Resort) this lovely home has a ton to offer the winter enthusiast! With 242 ft of shoreline on Tait Lake, enjoy cross country skiing on the lake or snowshoeing the established trails that meander around the Tait Lake area. Or just cozy up to the nice wood burning fireplace and enjoy the views of Tait Lake from the Great room.  Meander down the winding driveway and forget about everything but being at the lake! Gorgeous level access with a well manicured boreal forest surrounding the lovely cabin overlooking Tait Lake. Walk on to the entry deck to the home and smell the fresh air, soak in the lake views! Enter in to the Great room and feel that comforting welcome this homes gives to all who enter! Kitchen is perfect for entertaining with new quartz counters, sunken sink, new Maytag Fridge and Stove...all ready for you to prepare those family meals at the cabin! Open concept dining area, Great room with NICE lake views and wood burning fireplace. Enjoy morning coffee on the three season porch, with wonderful wilderness AND lake views, very cozy and comfy. Two bedrooms and a huge bathroom AND a laundry room complete the main level of the home! A wide kid friendly stairs welcomes you to the upper loft area, with great lake views and plenty of space for a master bedroom or bunk space to sleep the masses! Closets are a plenty on both levels, great storage in this home!  The land is well established with walking paths meandering the home and leading you to the lake, a beautiful setting with nice level access to the lake with a year round crib dock. A one and a half car garage (really great for boat storage!) completes the package.  This Lutsen Lake home has it all!

description: For sale: $171,000. Perfect Year Round vacation Home. Ski in and Ski Out location, within a few minutes of the Superior National Golf course, direct access to hiking trails, snowmobile trails and biking on Forest roads and Gitchi Gammi State Biking Trail. Property management company is available on site if you choose to rent and is completely hassle free for the owner. Nice way to offset some of the cost of maintaining a second home.  This townhome has three levels with full size kitchen open to the living room and a deck overlooking Moose Mountain. Nice stone fireplace near dining area adds to the ambiance while gathering for meals.  Master Loft style Bedroom with a Bathroom for privacy is situated upstairs. The lower level features 2 bedrooms and a bathroom. Caribou Highlands offers indoor and outdoor swimming pools, relax by the pool or go for a hike. Moguls Restaurant is located right in the main lodge, offering delicious food and drinks.  New siding is being installed this year

description: For sale: $229,000. Newer Home on the Honeymoon Trail in Lutsen! Christine Lake public access is nearby, snowmobile trail is down the road - quick access to White Pine Lake and other lakes in Lutsen. Federal and State Land is accessible within walking distance, endless hiking and exploring opportunities. Perfect Home for year round living in a private setting or to have North Shore adventures home base. Bright Home full of light on one level. Newly built in 2015 with super functional floor plan - featuring kitchen with lots of storage and countertop space, open to a spacious living room. Spectacular view of the forest, right out of the living room. The Master bedroom with a nice walk in closet, plenty of room for all your seasonal clothes. The second bedroom is perfect for guests or to use as an office or workout room.  This home has laundry area, conveniently located in the entry way and near the kitchen. There is plenty of storage room in the crawl space, exceeding the minimum required height - new owner could put plenty of shelves.  2 cars detached garage and a shed complete the package! This property has everything - location and newer construction!

Stay and play in this one bedroom unit with an open sleeping loft, unit sleeps six. description: Recently sold: $475,000. Serenity is THIS Lutsen Clara Lake home. Wilderness setting yet only 20 min. to Lutsen Mountains Ski Resort! Clara Lake is a nice walleye lake, lots of structure & an island for wildlife attraction. The Superior National Forest protects the view shed of this lovely lake home. And that's what this home is all about, the incredible Lake views from nearly every room in the home. Even the galley style large kitchen has views! The Great Room will WOW you with Views and Vaulted Ceiling, featuring Open family and dining room, and fireplace. Super Sunroom, w/ lakeside deck for casual summer dining. Main level is finished off with a nice bedroom, bath and laundry area. The Upper level is fantastic! A Romantic Owner's Suite w/ loft library, large bedrm w/ gas fireplace, screened deck and a WOWSER of a master bath complete with soaking tub. description: Recently sold: $196,000. Welcome to Pike Lake, miles of cool, pure water. This charming property is on the west end of Pike: the quiet side. Step inside the spacious A-frame: paneled floors and walls are warm and inviting, earnest wood stove. A bank of lakeside windows tells of every mood of light. A skylight highlights meals and the days planning. Birch branch cabinet fronts provide a Northwoods design sensibility. 240 of lakeshore, with a view to the east of the entire length of the lake. Property abuts public land. No other structures are visible from the cabin. The neighbors are a bit wild: pine marten, moose, bear, fox. Serenity is the concept here. Theres also plenty to do: the fishing is fantastic on Pike. Cross Country ski or snowmobile for miles. The forest is diverse with enough sugar maple to splash some color, heck do some syruping! Power, fiber optic and year round access are just the right dose of civilization. Lutsen is down the road. Back lot with 9 additional acres also available.
